Load, install, and manage agent bundles from the Musher Hub.
Browse bundles, run them ephemerally, or install assets into
your project's harness directory.

Get started:  mush bundle load

Usage:
  mush [flags]
  mush [command]

Examples:
  mush bundle load acme/my-kit

Bundle Commands:
  bundle      Manage agent bundles

Account & Configuration:
  auth        Manage authentication
  config      Manage configuration
  history     Inspect transcript history from PTY sessions

Setup & Diagnostics:
  completion  Generate shell completion scripts
  doctor      Diagnose common issues
  init        Setup Mush for first use
  paths       Show where Mush stores files
  update      Update mush to the latest version
  version     Show version information

Advanced:
  habitat     Manage habitats
  worker      Manage the local worker runtime

Additional Commands:
  help        Help about any command

Flags:
      --api-key string   API key override (prefer MUSH_API_KEY env var)
      --api-url string   Override Musher API URL for this command
  -h, --help             help for mush
      --json             Output in JSON format
      --no-color         Disable colored output
      --no-input         Disable interactive prompts
      --no-tui           Disable interactive TUI navigation
      --quiet            Minimal output (for CI)

Use "mush [command] --help" for more information about a command.
